      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MRS. MINIVER (4) finds it hard to win but looks close to breaking through. Continues to race well, filling the minors at the last four starts, the latest when third (29.90) at this track. Makes plenty of appeal. PULL THE TRIGGER (3) showed little early speed at his last couple, the latest finishing fourth (30.00) in a Grade 5 at this track. Good beginner aided by a nice draw. Has ability and a bold showing is expected. UNREAL STYLE (2) was safely held last time out, finishing sixth at this track over 515m behind Federal Felix (30.07) in a Grade 5. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Should be in this for a long way. RHONDA FULL DAY (1) was out of the money here last time out but can bounce back.",
